        {
          "name": "Step 2: Promote User to Admin (MongoDB Manual)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "INSTRUCTIONS - Run this in MongoDB:\n\n// Method 1: Using MongoDB Atlas UI\n1. Go to: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas\n2. Login to your account\n3. Click Browse Collections\n4. Select: lostandfound → users\n5. Find the user: admin@tip.edu.ph\n6. Click Edit (pencil icon)\n7. Change role from \"user\" to \"admin\"\n8. Click Update\n\n// Method 2: Using MongoDB Compass\n1. Download MongoDB Compass\n2. Connect with MONGO_URI\n3. Navigate to: lostandfound → users\n4. Find admin user\n5. Click Edit\n6. Change role to \"admin\"\n7. Click Update\n\n// Method 3: Using MongoDB Shell\ndb.users.updateOne(\n  { email: \"admin@tip.edu.ph\" },\n  { $set: { role: \"admin\" } }\n)\n\nExpected Response:\n{ acknowledged: true, modifiedCount: 1 }\n\n✅ Done! User is now admin",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "text"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "me"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 3: Verify Admin Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
